<subSubSection id="DB7CCB3791CE6D77426BFF0B245BC379" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8521371C319C5CA6CE29187CA06ED02C" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">Type</paragraph>
<paragraph id="18A2F16BA940A7B400D49086E2AC100C" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">
(holotype indicated by 
<bibRefCitation id="DE4759874B6CDBC3D7578926C73E17E2" author="Zohary, M" journalOrPublisher="The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem" pageId="15" pageNumber="22" refId="B62" refString="Zohary, M, Heller, D, 1984. The Genus Trifolium. The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem" title="The Genus Trifolium." year="1984">Zohary and Heller 1984</bibRefCitation>
: 283). In ins. Lissa, in campo grande 4 (Plate 12, Figure 1 in 
<bibRefCitation id="E38280E1DD918E1D5EE082AECA1FD343" author="Portenschlag-Ledermayer, F von" journalOrPublisher="Wien" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" refId="B47" refString="Portenschlag-Ledermayer, F von, 1824. Enumeratio plantarum in Dalmatia lectarum. Wien" title="Enumeratio plantarum in Dalmatia lectarum" year="1824">Portenschlag-Ledermayer 1824</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E6897BEF18BEEBB4B2E05E28170D2329" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph id="89F90B445FD5701BB19A0A76A53B9E88" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD8F11F1A81188F33447F121FBECD9D1" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">
Heads large, fruiting calyx tubular, longitudinal nerves barely visible in the distal portion; corolla&gt; than twice as long as the calyx tube, seeds irregularly ovoid, light brown (
<figureCitation id="01CC3ECAA47446821D23D7AB8920A928" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Comparison between mature calyces of Trifolium subsect. Mystillus species in Italy (bar = 1 mm). Left: Trifolium vesiculosum (A) and Trifolium spumosum (A '), middle Trifolium multistriatum transitional (B) and typical (B ') forms, right Trifolium mutabile s. str. (C) and Trifolium mutabile var. gussoneanum (C ')." figureDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.2.10361.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/106589" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" tableDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.2.10361.figure2">Figures 2C</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="EA31047D00E13CECF2EC6FC9E3D40B01" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Trifolium mutabile collected in Viterbo (bar = 1 mm). Flowers (15 May 2015), seeds (15 July 2016)." figureDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.2.10361.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/106591" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" tableDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.2.10361.figure4">4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="88F88E06D0DD2AC8D7C977DF7CD0DA6B" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A5AF0856E8089C64A3002BC951409B23" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">Updated geographical distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="94F8B0681748FD9817A16B48574CC688" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">Liguria: 0A, Tuscany: +A (new), Umbria: +A (new), Lazio: +A (new), Campania: 0 (new), Apulia: +, Basilicata: 0 (new), Calabria: +, Sicily: +.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9EE4999C380B4E777AAFA3B5AB9B0C48" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" type="notes">
<paragraph id="6775CE854AA6FC05618077B0AD1EB672" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="06CA2F7D4DD63759D05C6325979963B8" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">
Species endemic to the Mediterranean area (
<bibRefCitation id="D16A515D338D9C3877AAB20912050B9E" author="Greuter, W" journalOrPublisher="Conservatoire et Jardin Botaniques, Geneve" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B25" refString="Greuter, W, Burdet, HM, Long, G, 1989. Med-Checklist 4. Conservatoire et Jardin Botaniques, Geneve" title="Med-Checklist 4." year="1989">Greuter et al. 1989</bibRefCitation>
), which was described for Dalmatia. In the wild it is widespread in the western Balkans (Dalmatia, Greece, Albania) and in southern Italy, from Campania to Sicily (
<bibRefCitation id="FD99D17FF01EEC1BDCB4DECC4DB9B1A2" author="Ellison, NW" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" publicationUrl="http://ww2.bgbm.org/EuroPlusMed/" refId="B15" refString="2006 onwards. Euro+Med PlantBase-the information resource for Euro-Mediterranean plant diversity.http://ww2.bgbm.org/EuroPlusMed/" title="Euro + Med PlantBase-the information resource for Euro-Mediterranean plant diversity" url="http://ww2.bgbm.org/EuroPlusMed/" year="2006 onwards">Euro+Med 2006 onwards</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="92CAD3DDE0B4E2B47B00AD7B93746C50" author="Conti, F" journalOrPublisher="Palombi Editori, Roma" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B8" refString="Conti, F, Abbate, G, Alessandrini, A, Blasi, C, 2005. An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora. Palombi Editori, Roma" title="An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora." year="2005">Conti et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
), where it is represented by 
<taxonomicName id="501EA079062368DC2B3C989A5B34A554" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium mutabile var. gussoneanum" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="mutabile" variety="gussoneanum">Trifolium mutabile var. gussoneanum</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="C87FBC37C1D86DE1C3EE6D49B74A1908" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Comparison between mature calyces of Trifolium subsect. Mystillus species in Italy (bar = 1 mm). Left: Trifolium vesiculosum (A) and Trifolium spumosum (A '), middle Trifolium multistriatum transitional (B) and typical (B ') forms, right Trifolium mutabile s. str. (C) and Trifolium mutabile var. gussoneanum (C ')." figureDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.2.10361.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/106589" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" tableDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.2.10361.figure2">Figure 2C</figureCitation>
'), endemic to southern Italy 
<normalizedToken id="FF506106ED84379CFD66082AF30FDEC4" originalValue="“…">&quot;...</normalizedToken>
Varietas haec T. mutabilem cum 
<taxonomicName id="9C6CC954B7DBE1237F65E956F403872B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium multistriatum" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multistriatum">Trifolium multistriatum</taxonomicName>
ideo conjungit.&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="9A3FEF84B5D2B25DAE7043B1ECC794C4" author="Gibelli, G" journalOrPublisher="Memorie della Reale accademia delle scienze di Torino (serie 2)" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" pagination="179 - 222" refId="B23" refString="Gibelli, G, Belli, S, 1892. Rivista critica delle specie di Trifolium italiane comparate con quelle del resto d'Europa e delle regioni circummediterranee della sezione Trigantheum Nobis (Mistyllus Presl. p.p.). Memorie della Reale accademia delle scienze di Torino (serie 2) 42: 179 - 222" title="Rivista critica delle specie di Trifolium italiane comparate con quelle del resto d'Europa e delle regioni circummediterranee della sezione Trigantheum Nobis (Mistyllus Presl. p. p.)." volume="42" year="1892">Gibelli and Belli 1892</bibRefCitation>
). The Sicilian authors propose to rank it as subspecies (Brullo in 
<bibRefCitation id="B6E6959F8F04D34DECF51F7FCD539851" author="La Rosa, A" journalOrPublisher="Universita degli Studi di Palermo" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" refId="B30" refString="La Rosa, A, 2011. Indagini tassonomiche, ecologiche e distributive sul genere Trifolium L. in Sicilia. Universita degli Studi di Palermo" title="Indagini tassonomiche, ecologiche e distributive sul genere Trifolium L. in Sicilia" year="2011">La Rosa 2011</bibRefCitation>
). The presence of 
<taxonomicName id="3FF9301628E5C152E8A549F84CE34D75" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium mutabile" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mutabile">
<emphasis id="A2F52E2C308F69D714E37889526B849F" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">Trifolium mutabile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Iberian Peninsula is most likely occasional (
<bibRefCitation id="5926EAD04FC1B8D96EC3395509DF9671" author="Munoz, A" journalOrPublisher="Monografias del Instituto Pirenaico de Ecologia" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" pagination="293 - 300" refId="B40" refString="Munoz, A, Devesa, JA, 1988. Trifoliumsect.Mystillus (C.Presl) Godron en Espana. Monografias del Instituto Pirenaico de Ecologia 4: 293 - 300" title="Trifoliumsect. Mystillus (C. Presl) Godron en Espana." volume="4" year="1988">
<normalizedToken id="3B2DB321847D84C76333545AD6752928" originalValue="Muñoz">Munoz</normalizedToken>
and Devesa 1988
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="2BCEA084D2D9398D14FD2D462702F123" author="Greuter, W" journalOrPublisher="Conservatoire et Jardin Botaniques, Geneve" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B25" refString="Greuter, W, Burdet, HM, Long, G, 1989. Med-Checklist 4. Conservatoire et Jardin Botaniques, Geneve" title="Med-Checklist 4." year="1989">Greuter et al. 1989</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1368925A3BA08EE9B530890FF5C47593" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">
Here, we report it for the first time in central Italy both in the countryside south of Manciano (Grosseto), where it was found to be abundant in fallow and resting fields as well as wood edges, and in the outskirts of Castel Giorgio and of Orvieto (Terni), not far from the Lazio border, where it was observed in small populations of fallow fields and roadsides. In both stations, together with the one recently reported in Lazio (
<bibRefCitation id="A2BACC6B63114B64438663462508842A" author="Lopez Tirado, J" editor="Bartolucci, F" journalOrPublisher="Informatore Botanico Italiano" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" pagination="222 - 223" refId="B33" refString="Lopez Tirado, J, Manzano Gutierrez, F, Scoppola, A, 2015. Notula: 2139. In: Bartolucci, F, Nepi, C, Domina, G, Peruzzi, L, Eds., Notulae alla Checklist della Flora Vascolare Italiana: 20 (2130-2158). . Informatore Botanico Italiano 47: 222 - 223" title="Notula: 2139." volume="47" volumeTitle="Notulae alla Checklist della Flora Vascolare Italiana: 20 (2130 - 2158)." year="2015">Lopez Tirado et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
), the species is believed to be a naturalized alien. In central Italy, it is used as forage in multiple crops with 
<taxonomicName id="32CD3529F8BE7118316DD4EA260A2826" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium squarrosum" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="squarrosum">
<emphasis id="6BD86F0DD77063D69A0CCA0ED8D4A4EC" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">Trifolium squarrosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. or 
<taxonomicName id="466F9A3B3C2DB4B5FBB732CF19BF9073" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium incarnatum" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="incarnatum">
<emphasis id="D7DD9E7FA8BF7031C55AB76230050C7E" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">Trifolium incarnatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. in arid localities (e.g. San Lazzaro, Viterbo) where it escapes from cultivation. As a non-native species it was reported in Liguria by 
<bibRefCitation id="ABC0CCBEE7D942790718B32B5F9F9E88" author="Fiori, A" journalOrPublisher="Flora analitica d'Italia" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" pagination="57 - 58" refId="B18" refString="Fiori, A, Paoletti, G, 1900. . Flora analitica d'Italia 2: 57 - 58" volume="2" year="1900">Fiori and Paoletti (1900)</bibRefCitation>
but never confirmed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="790A1D1423ED90A7B8B9A7047B9BAAF1" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName id="9695AA1E0CDCFE2AC79C7C9B4610D7CC" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium mutabile" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mutabile">
<emphasis id="05AE0C8C6A0B6EAA62BB54D5FCF4D989" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">Trifolium mutabile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known in Campania (
<bibRefCitation id="BA2A2A9810B497F92B0939641277189B" author="Conti, F" journalOrPublisher="Palombi Editori, Roma" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B8" refString="Conti, F, Abbate, G, Alessandrini, A, Blasi, C, 2005. An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora. Palombi Editori, Roma" title="An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora." year="2005">Conti et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
), where it was reported from Roccamonfina (Caserta) by 
<bibRefCitation id="898650BC5DC9889E45F4439FEBB181BE" author="Croce, A" journalOrPublisher="Webbia" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" pagination="251 - 291" publicationUrl="10.1080/00837792.2008.10670844" refId="B11" refString="Croce, A, La Valva, V, Motti, R, Nazzaro, R, Strumia, S, 2008. La flora del Vulcano di Roccamonfina (Campania, Italia). Webbia 63: 251 - 291" title="La flora del Vulcano di Roccamonfina (Campania, Italia)." url="10.1080/00837792.2008.10670844" volume="63" year="2008">Croce et al. (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, although samples are not available. Here we repeatedly looked for it in the outskirts of the Masseria S. Anna but were only able to find 
<taxonomicName id="B39F6F452789F2D7F5527DDD308C11EE" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium vesiculosum" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vesiculosum">
<emphasis id="09F8DDADCB8D00D37CA4AB87BBCC6BF7" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">Trifolium vesiculosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Nevertheless, two different historical samples collected in the Campi Flegrei area by Nicola Terracciano (NAP!) and near the Lake of Agnano by Heldreich in 1840 (FI!, revised by Gibelli and Belli as 
<taxonomicName id="43F8070789111B82694CF4AF2B0071C9" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="mutabile var. gussoneanum" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="mutabile" variety="gussoneanum">var. gussoneanum</taxonomicName>
) belong to this species. Thus, the presence of the species in Campania deserves to be confirmed. It is considered as occurring in Apulia by 
<bibRefCitation id="C1FEDB1D3C534528E30F16DB568B6096" author="Conti, F" journalOrPublisher="Palombi Editori, Roma" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B8" refString="Conti, F, Abbate, G, Alessandrini, A, Blasi, C, 2005. An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora. Palombi Editori, Roma" title="An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora." year="2005">Conti et al. (2005)</bibRefCitation>
based on 
<bibRefCitation id="BA9D4440E954ECA9DB5A84238CDD5CD1" author="Pignatti, S" journalOrPublisher="Edagricole, Bologna" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" pagination="721 - 741" refId="B45" refString="Pignatti, S, 1982. Flora d'Italia. Edagricole, Bologna: 721 - 741" title="Flora d'Italia" year="1982">Pignatti (1982)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="A747B71000533B926BCA9621DF55977D" author="Fiori, A" journalOrPublisher="Nuova Flora Analitica d'Italia" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" pagination="859 - 860" refId="B17" refString="Fiori, A, 1925. . Nuova Flora Analitica d'Italia 1: 859 - 860" volume="1" year="1925">Fiori (1925</bibRefCitation>
, RO!) and by 
<bibRefCitation id="C518C6D0EAC271BA6D56A3CA97033ED5" author="Mele, C" journalOrPublisher="Flora Mediterranea" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" pagination="193 - 245" refId="B38" refString="Mele, C, Medagli, P, Accogli, R, Beccarisi, L, Albano, A, Marchiori, S, 2006. Flora of Salento (Apulia, Southeastern Italy): an annotated checklist. Flora Mediterranea 16: 193 - 245" title="Flora of Salento (Apulia, Southeastern Italy): an annotated checklist." volume="16" year="2006">Mele et al. (2006)</bibRefCitation>
; it was also collected by P. Medagli (LEC!).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F136EC10FB1C35B28109A8E58D2AFBD2" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">
Finally, the current presence of 
<taxonomicName id="3A82626452273953D49B29B74806C256" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium mutabile" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mutabile">
<emphasis id="E3848246FDF66AA927B7CD0130373A12" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">Trifolium mutabile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Basilicata (
<bibRefCitation id="9E7A6613C54C91777359B9816213E692" author="Conti, F" journalOrPublisher="Palombi Editori, Roma" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B8" refString="Conti, F, Abbate, G, Alessandrini, A, Blasi, C, 2005. An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora. Palombi Editori, Roma" title="An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora." year="2005">Conti et al 2005</bibRefCitation>
) needs confirmation, since it is only based on the specimens reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="28528F71834C0B79838F39CFDC4F19B4" author="Gavioli, O" journalOrPublisher="Nuovo Giornale Botanico Italiano (nuova serie)" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" pagination="134 - 135" refId="B20" refString="Gavioli, O, 1948. Synopsis Florae Lucanae. Nuovo Giornale Botanico Italiano (nuova serie) 54: 134 - 135" title="Synopsis Florae Lucanae." volume="54" year="1948">Gavioli (1948)</bibRefCitation>
as a variety of 
<taxonomicName id="A32A3C850D6A3DA482DD8671A73D0865" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium vesiculosum" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vesiculosum">
<emphasis id="3BABD612552E54037A9FA2CFC25CC750" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">Trifolium vesiculosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(kept in FI! and revised by us as 
<taxonomicName id="FF95FEA4DBFA3F03B3FD3EB8EDE63F62" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium mutabile var. gussoneanum" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="mutabile" variety="gussoneanum">Trifolium mutabile var. gussoneanum</taxonomicName>
), dating back to the 1930s.
</paragraph>
